    {
      "text": "1989 tarot card reading simulation",
      "lang": "en",
      "source": "wikidata"
    },
    {
      "text": "Taboo: The Sixth Sense is a tarot card reading simulation developed by Rare and published by Tradewest for the Nintendo Entertainment System (NES) in 1989.\nTaboo gives users a tarot reading where the \"dealer\" automatically shuffles the cards. It is the only NES game to carry two warnings: that it is for players ages fourteen and older and is also for entertainment purposes only. Taboo was marketed as a party game that multiple adults could enjoy simultaneously.",
      "lang": "en",
      "source": "wikipedia_en"
    },
    {
      "text": "Taboo: The Sixth Sence (Tabú: El Sexto Sentido) es un videojuego desarrollado por Rare y publicado por Tradewest para Nintendo Entertainment System en 1988.​​",
      "lang": "es",
      "source": "wikipedia_es"
    },
    {
      "text": "Taboo: The Sixth Sense è un videogioco di simulazione di tarocchi sviluppato da Rare e pubblicato nel 1989 da Tradewest per Nintendo Entertainment System. Le musiche del gioco sono state composte da David Wise.",
      "lang": "it",
      "source": "wikipedia_it"
    },
    {
      "text": "『タブー：第六感』は、Rareが開発し、Tradewestが1989年に任天堂のファミリーコンピュータ（NES）向けに発売したタロットカード占いシミュレーションゲームです。\n本作では、「ディーラー」が自動でカードをシャッフルし、タロットのリーディングを提供します。このゲームは、14歳以上を対象とし、かつ娯楽目的のみであることを警告する、唯一のNESゲームでした。タブーは、複数の大人が同時に楽しめるパーティーゲームとして販売されました。",
      "lang": "ja",
      "source": "ai_local_gemma4",
      "base_lang": "en"
    }
  ]
